<P>
   Technology folk are not known for their love of natural light,
let alone the great outdoors. Boats seem to be an exception.
</P>
<P>
   The influence of technology gurus such as Bill Gates
(Microsoft), Larry Ellison (Oracle) and Jim Clark (Netscape), all
owners of extremely sleek sail or power yachts, cannot be
discounted.
</P>
<P>
   Durant says he saw a flow diagram published recently showing the
steps to going public. One of the steps was ``Order new yacht.''
</P>
<P>
   A good deal of this watery enthusiasm has been sated on borrowed
money.
