<P>
   CYBERSEX _ There's nothing sexy about a computer, unless people
are using it to log onto porn sites, or flirt and more in chat
rooms. A symposium in Atlanta is exploring what cybersex does to
relationships in the real world; topics include cybersex abusers
and treatment, infidelity online, virtual sex addiction and effects
on the couple relationship. (Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
10.
</P>
<P>
   HOT-CHEF _ COMMERCE, Ga. _ Sue and Jeg Coughlin of Columbus,
Ohio have six race cars on the National Hot Rod racing circuit.
With crew, friends and an expanding family traveling the circuit,
the Coughlins soon grew tired of the tacky track food. So they
hired a chef. Not just any chef, but Ian Rough, a brand new
graduate of the Culinary Institute of America, the most prestigious
cooking school in America. Rough customized a trailer to meet his
gourmet cooking needs and now he's on the road with the Coughlin
crew. We visit with him and the family in Commerce on the weekend
of the NHRA races to soak in the scene (and taste some of Rough's
track cuisine.) (RWalker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12. WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   COLLECTIBLES _ ATLANTA _ We are a nation of collectors, and the
South is catching on in a big way. The Southeast racked up $2
billion in collectible sales for 1998, a growing corner of the
market that tallies $10 billion annually. So it's no wonder the
International Collectible Exposition has turned its attention to
Atlanta. The prestigous show will be making its Southern debut at
the Georgia World Congress Center today and Sunday. (Brooks,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12. WITH PHOTO.
