</P>
<P>
   ETIQUETTE-SCHOOLS (Quincy, Mass.) _ Manners classes like the one
run by Judi Vankevich are examples of a growing children's
etiquette movement around the country, one that goes beyond table
manners and borrows from the old school of decorum as parents
despair over how clueless kids are today in social settings. By
Linda Matchan. 1240 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   BEAM-COLUMN (Undated) -- The World's Second Greatest University
is much on my mind as I prepare for my 25th Yale reunion later this
month. By Alex Beam.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-AFRICA (Undated) _ Like ``Out of Africa,'' with which it
