<P>
   Photo and graphics information and editors' names can be found
at the end of this budget.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ A progress report at the
halfway point in a bruising, very partisan, two-week Senate dehate
over a Republican bill that rejects President Clinton's approach to
shaping federal aid to schools over the next five years. The bill
would re-authorize the Elementary and Secondary Education Act.
(Mollison, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-QUOTES _ scratched. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   CENSUS-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ Republican House members and
Census Director Kenneth Prewitt clashed at a hearing Friday over
whether Prewitt had politicized the count by citing GOP complaints
that the census long form was overly intrusive. (Holmes, Cox News
Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   LIPSTADT-HOLOCAUST _ WASHINGTON _ Deborah Lipstadt, Emory
University professor and author of ``Denying the Holocaust,''
discusses the ``The Holocaust: The Continuing Challenge for
Contemporary Ethics'' Friday at the American Jewish Committees
annual meeting and International Leadership Conference on domestic
and international concerns. Developing. (Schultz, Cox News
Service). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6 p.m. EDT in (i) International and (w)
Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-LEBANON _ KIRYAT SHEMONA, Israel _ From the rubble in
this town near Israel's northern border to a funeral for an Israeli
soldier killed just across that border, Israelis here confronted
the harsh realities Friday of their dilemma of whether to withdraw
from southern Lebanon. Two days of fighting appeared to be calming
down also Friday, as international pressure was brought to bear
against both sides to end the shelling. But tensions along the
border remain high. Developing. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 4 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-PUTIN (Scratched)
</P>
<P>
   ATTN EDs: The inauguration date has been moved back to Sun., May
7.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-POLITICS _ When the pundits were pondering whether
religion would play much of a role in this year's presidential
election, most forgot to ask a pretty fundamental question: Which
religion? As it turns out, Roman Catholic voters are at center
stage this year. (Baxter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (p) Politics and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   POL-TICKER _ A brief roundup of the day's campaign events,
pulled from Cox staff and wire reports. (Cox News Service) ETA: 6
p.m.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-LEWIS-RULING _ ATLANTA _ Judge set to rule today on motion
for severances in the case of Baltimore Ravens' All-Pro linebacker
Ray Lewis.. If answer is no, as seems likely, it should clear the
way for May 15 trial for all defendants. Lewis is charged in the
double slaying of two men in Atlanta in the hours after the Super
Bowl. (Tory, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
