<SLUG> BC-CHURCH-HATE0506-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Churches that hate have no love of God
 &HT;    By Steve Gushee
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Many churches need someone to hate.
</P>
<P>
   Religious groups have grown strong by promoting hatred in the
name of a God of love. But their behavior is in absolute
contradiction to the God they profess to serve.
</P>
<P>
   The latest example is a small religious community in West Palm
Beach that calls itself the Eternal Gospel Church of Seventh-day
Adventists.
</P>
<P>
   The 70-member church calls Jesus Lord by preaching hatred of
Roman Catholics.
</P>
<P>
   Their vocal ranting against the Roman Catholic Church is so
vitriolic that the national denomination of Seventh-day Adventists
went to court to deny them the right to use their name.
</P>
<P>
   The denomination of nearly 1 million people, which has tempered
its own once-venomous prejudice of Catholicism, won the judgment.
Still, the local church plans to ignore the order and continue to
use the name.
</P>
<P>
   Seventh-day Adventists observe the Jewish Sabbath, the seventh
day of the week, rather than Sunday as their day of worship. The
denomination has long taught that the pope and fourth-century
Emperor Constantine invented Sunday as the Lord's Day in a vast
self-serving conspiracy contrary to God's will.
</P>
<P>
   That is the basis of their anti-Catholic rancor, which, at
times, has identified the pope with the Antichrist, Satan and the
dread Beast of the Book of Revelation.
</P>
<P>
   In recent years, the denomination has made significant effort to
be less narrow-minded, though the teaching about Sunday is
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
   The Seventh-day Advent movement began in 1844. Founder Ellen
Wright gathered the remnant of a group that was in despair when the
world did not end as they expected. From that ``great
disappointment,'' the church grew.
</P>
<P>
   But Adventists are not alone in preaching hatred. Bob Jones
University, the popular Christian college in South Carolina, has a
long history of anti-Catholic bias and racial prejudice warmly
embraced in the name of God. Some pro-life believers insist God
hates doctors who perform legal abortions. Some Orthodox Jews argue
that God hates the Reform and Conservative Jewish traditions.
</P>
<P>
   The Rev. Billy Graham is the most famous of a generation of
religious leaders who became popular preaching God's hatred of
communism in the '50s. Now that that philosophy is passe, many
churches, in need of a new scapegoat to hate, concentrate on
homosexuals.
</P>
<P>
   The anti-Catholic prejudice of the Eternal Gospel Church is
outrageous but relatively insignificant because the church itself
is insignificant.
</P>
<P>
   Religious hatred by mainline Protestant, Catholic and Jewish
traditions are more outrageous and far more dangerous.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
