Airport, which it says would substantially lower fares on the
popular route. AirTran now flies to Dulles but cannot serve
National because of slot controls. The new federal aviation act
creates 12 slow exemptions for service to medium and small markets.
AirTran argues its Atlanta flights would qualify because pax could
connect at Hartsfield to smaller cities. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
