<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (For release on May 12, 2000) 
 
 
By MICHAEL LONSFORD 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Today is Limerick Day. The five-line humorous poems were
popularized by whom? &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   This week's worthy wine is a winner
</P>
<P>
   It would go great with a barbecue dinner.
</P>
<P>
   It has pepper and spice
</P>
<P>
   And such a great price
</P>
<P>
   Your wallet won't get noticeably thinner.
</P>
<P>
   The 1996 Santa Joana Bairrada Reserva _ four stars _ is an
attractive red wine from Portugal that does indeed have a Rhonelike
briar-and-pepper spiciness that would match up very well with spicy
meats and sauces.
</P>
<P>
   And you cannot beat the $6.99 price.
</P>
<P>
   Answer: English artist and author Edward Lear, born on this day
in 1812.
</P>
<P>
