   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, May 5 --
Pennsylvania State University Applied Research Laboratory of
University Park won a $249,875 contract from Office of Naval
Research in Arlington, Va., for research and development.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $81,566 contract from
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for aircraft and
airframe structural components.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $56,760 contract from
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engines,
turbines and components.
</P>
<P>
   Night Vision Equipment Company of Allentown won a $99,960
contract from Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for
communication, detection and coherent radiation equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Bec Machine Products Inc. of Harlysville won a $63,200 contract
from Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for pipe, tubing,
hose and fittings.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $62,437 contract from
Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia, Pa., for hardware
and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Helicopters of Ridley Park won a $81,566 contract from
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for aircraft and
airframe structural components.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $56,760 contract from
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engines,
turbines and components.
</P>
<P>
   Night Vision Equipment Company of Allentown won a $99,960
contract from Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for
communication, detection and coherent radiation equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Bec Machine Products Inc. of Harlysville won a $63,200 contract
from Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for pipe, tubing,
hose and fittings.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $62,437 contract from
