<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-05 18:25 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7027 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l BC-CYBERSEX-QUIZ06-COX     05-05 0458
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CYBERSEX-QUIZ06-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The CAI, or Cybersexual Addiction Index
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   This quiz was put together by the Center for Online Addiction.
Its Web site is www.netaddiction .com.
</P>
<P>
   Answer each question on a 0-5 point scale; 0 is not applicable,
1 is rarely, 2 is occasionally, 3 is frequently, 4 is often, and 5
is always.
</P>
<P>
   1. How often do you neglect other responsibilities to spend more
time involved in cybersex?
</P>
<P>
   2. How often do you prefer cybersex to sexual intimacy with your
partner?
</P>
<P>
   3. How often do you spend significant amounts of time in chat
rooms and private messaging with the sole purpose of finding
cybersex?
</P>
<P>
   4. How often do others in your life complain about the amount of
time you spend online?
</P>
<P>
   5. How often does your job performance or productivity suffer
because of cybersex activities at work?
</P>
<P>
   6. How often do you become defensive or secretive when anyone
asks you what you do online?
</P>
<P>
   7. How often do you become anxious, nervous or upset when you
are unable to access sexually oriented Web sites?
</P>
<P>
   8. How often do you fear that life without cybersex would be
boring, empty and joyless?
</P>
<P>
   9. How often do you masturbate during cybersex?
</P>
<P>
   10. How often do you snap, yell or act annoyed if someone
bothers you while you are online?
</P>
<P>
   11. How often do you lose sleep due to late night log-ins having
cybersex?
</P>
<P>
   12. How often do you feel preoccupied with cybersex when offline
and/or fantasize about cybersex when offline?
</P>
<P>
   13. How often do you bookmark or subscribe to sexually oriented
Web sites?
</P>
<P>
   14. How often do you use cybersex as a reward for accomplishing
something?
</P>
<P>
   15. How often do you use anonymous communication to engage in
sexual fantasies not typically carried out in real life?
</P>
<P>
   16. How often do you anticipate your next online session with
the expectation that you will find sexual arousal or gratification?
</P>
<P>
   17. How often do you hide your online sexual interactions from
your significant other?
</P>
<P>
   18. How often do you move from cybersex to phone sex or
real-life meetings?
</P>
<P>
   19. How often do you feel guilty or shameful after cybersex?
</P>
<P>
   20. How often do you engage in deceptive or devious online
sexual behavior?
</P>
<P>
   Severity of impairment index:
</P>
<P>
   None: 0-30
</P>
<P>
   Mild: 31-49
</P>
<P>
   Moderate: 50-79
</P>
<P>
   Severe: 80-100
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : The National Council on Sexual Addiction and
Compulsivity: www.ncsac.org
</P>
<P>
   The Center for On-Line Addiction: www.netaddiction.com
</P>
<P>
   San Jose Marital and Sexuality Centre: www.sex-centre.com
</P>
<P>
   Online Sexual Addiction Resource Center: www.onlinesexaddict.org
</P>
