The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, May 6. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
SUMMIT (Washington) - In what must surely be one of the most
enigmatic political moves of the presidential campaign, Arizona
Sen. John McCain now says he will attend the summit with Texas Gov.
George Bush on Tuesday in Pittsburgh but that he will not formally
endorse the Texan at that time. More than a few observers in the
GOP are shocked at what they consider to be humiliating treatment
of the party's presumptive nominee. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move
in the `A` category. &QL; 
