<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WINE-FOR-MOM-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A TOAST TO MOTHERS EVERYWHERE 
</HEADLINE>
   By LESLIE SBROCCO   
 WineToday.com  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   How much do I love you, Mom? Let me count the wines
</P>
<P>
   Syrah is for your power and strength. When you said, ``Be home
by 10 p.m.,'' you meant it.
</P>
<P>
   Pinot noir is for your elegance and style; ``classy'' is the one
word to describe you, Mom.
</P>
<P>
   Italian reds are for your passionate streak that includes
everything from endless hugs to occasional ``Wait until your father
gets home'' threats.
</P>
<P>
   Viognier is for your delicate, feminine side _ bubble baths and
shopping excursions with your daughters.
</P>
<P>
   Chardonnay is for your practical, dependable qualities. All
those diapers you've changed have to count for something.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, champagne is for your effervescence and wit. And just
because there's nothing better than bubbly to raise a glass in your
honor!
</P>
<P>
   How much do you love your mom? What about the mother of your
children?
</P>
<P>
   No, it's not a guilt trip but rather a reminder _ with Mother's
Day right around the corner on Sunday, May 14 _ that it's time to
think about a gift.
</P>
<P>
   Flowers are one way to go, clothes or jewelry another, but what
better way to say ``I love you'' than with a bottle of wine? Here
are some suggestions, with approximate retail prices, for an
oenological ode to Mom:
</P>
<P>
   Strong Syrahs
</P>
<P>
   _ Columbia Winery 1997 Syrah, 4 1/2 stars, $14.
</P>
<P>
   _ Stags' Leap Winery 1997 Syrah, 4 stars, $25.
</P>
<P>
   _ Anapamu Cellars 1998 Syrah, 4 stars, $16.
</P>
<P>
   Stylish Pinot Noirs
</P>
<P>
   _ Belles Souers 1998 Pinot Noir, 5 stars, $40.
</P>
<P>
   _ Adrian Fog 1998 Floodgate Pinot Noir, 4 1/2 stars, $45.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cambria 1997 Julia's Vineyard Pinot Noir, 4 stars, $24.
</P>
<P>
   Passionate Italians
</P>
<P>
   _ Aldo Conterno 1997 Barbera d'Alba, 4 stars, $20.
</P>
<P>
   _ Antinori 1996 ``Tignanello,'' 4 stars, $41.
</P>
<P>
   _ Poliziano Asinone 1996 Vino Nobile di Montepulciano, 4 stars,
$18.
</P>
<P>
   Pretty Viogniers
</P>
<P>
   _ Alain Paret et Gerard Depardieu, Lys de Volan Viognier, 5
stars, $43.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gregory Graham 1997 Viognier, 4 stars, $25.
</P>
<P>
   _ Callaway 1998 Viognier, 4 stars, $14.
</P>
<P>
   Dependable Chardonnays
</P>
<P>
   _ Laetitia Vineyards 1997 Chardonnay, 4 stars, $16.
</P>
<P>
   _ Iron Horse Vineyards 1997 ``Cuvee Joy'' Chardonnay, 4 stars,
$30.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fetzer ``Bonterra'' 1998 Chardonnay, 4 stars, $12.
</P>
<P>
   Best Bubblies
</P>
<P>
   _ Billecart-Salmon NV Brut Rose, 4 1/2 stars, $42
</P>
<P>
   _ Veuve Clicquot 1990 ``La Grande Dame,'' 5 stars, $135
</P>
<P>
   _ NV Mumm Cuvee Napa Blanc de Noir, 4 stars, $15
</P>
<P>
   (WineToday.com is a daily Internet publication of New York Times
Digital. Its Web address is www.winetoday.com.)
</P>
