<P>
   FRAGRANCE-BOUTIQUES (Undated) _ While customization has proved
popular recently in everything from suits to ice cream, it is
taking off in the top tiers of the fragrance industry. Creed, the
very upscale European fragrance house, offers custom scents at
Barneys New York, Bergdorf Goodman and Neiman Marcus. On the West
Coast there are a growing number of fragrance boutiques like Lather
in Pasadena and Homebody in Los Angeles that blend custom scents
for clients like K.D. Lang. By Alex Witchel.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-COPY-EDITORS (New York) _ Being a copy editor at a
women's fashion magazine _ and a male to boot _ is a little like
being the non-drinking, designated driver: you're around people
having a lot of fun, but you're not allowed to imbibe. Your job is
to make sure the semicolons are right; you don't get to pick up the
phone and trill ``Daaahling'' or air-kiss the French photographers
when they come in with their portfolios. By Ethan Hauser.
</P>
