   HEDGE-FUNDS (Undated) _ Money managers George Soros and Julian
H. Robertson Jr., who once rattled world financial markets with
mere hints of their actions, have lost much of their punch. But
hedge funds, the investment vehicles for the wealthy that these
prominent investors epitomized, are by no means on the ropes; the
unregulated hedge fund industry continues to grow. By Danny Hakim.
