<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, May 6, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   STOWAWAY-BODIES (Seattle) _ Chen Shaolin has a simple wish: She
wants to see her husband. An ocean stands between the Chinese woman
and Jiang Dainbiao, dead since January. But the Pacific is nothing
compared to the seeming indifference of two governments, and the
poverty in which Chen and her two children are mired.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde and Hsiao-Ching Chou.
</P>
<P>
   TV-VIKINGS (Undated) _ All of a sudden, Vikings are everywhere.
Hotter than the Dixie Chicks, they grace the covers of Time and
National Geographic, they're starring in a new Smithsonian road
show and a just-published companion book (``Vikings: The North
Atlantic Saga''), and _ here's a shock! _ they're on TV. Nothing
like PBS to stir the brew _ twice in eight days _ when there's
enlightenment to be had.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   WEB-MOVIE (Undated) _ SightSound.com is a Pennsylvania company
that specializes in downloadable movies and music. It's generated a
fair bit of buzz by billing ``Quantum Project'' as the first
``feature film'' to be made for and distributed exclusively on the
Web. Don't get your hopes up too high.
</P>
<P>
   By Winda Benedetti. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Salt Lake City) _ Sonics vs. Jazz in Game 5 for the
right to advance into the NBA Western Conference semifinals against
the Portland Trail Blazers.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-THIEL-COLUMN (Salt Lake City) _ Column from the Sonics-Jazz
game.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host Anaheim Angels.
</P>
<P>
   By John Hickey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
