age in a world that pays much more attention to the needs of those
ahead of them or behind them. By Fred Brock.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-HEALTH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Money &AMP; Medicine: Ask people how
money is wasted in the health care system, and their tone of voice
will undergo an interesting change. Doctors huff and puff about the
squadrons of workers they have had to hire to meet the paperwork
demands of managed care. Patients complain about the $60 they shell
out for three-minute appointments during which doctors seems to do
little more than blink at them. Insurance companies bemoan
unnecessary tests. In fact, there are many quantifiable ways that
millions of dollars go up in smoke each year. Patients are
complicit in the process, though they do not always know it. By
Jennifer Steinhauer.
