   INTERNET-PRIVACY (Undated) _ There has been no shortage of
discussion about how the Internet is stripping consumers of what
thin veil of privacy they have left in this world of credit bureaus
and supermarket scanners. But lost in this debate is just how
ineffective most of these data-gathering systems have been. Sure,
