pulling out their wiry hair trying to keep up with the diversity of
the four-wheeled kingdom. Should one, for instance, accept BMW's
classification of its X5 as a ``sport activity vehicle''? Is that
different from an ``all activity vehicle,'' which is what Mercedes
calls its M-Class? Whatever term should come of age, it had better
grow up quick, since five- and six-passenger pickups with four
sedan-style doors and shortened cargo beds are barging into the
market like an enraged SWAT team. By Dan Neil.
</P>
