 &HT;    WIRE EDITORS, BUSINESS EDITORS, MANAGING EDITORS:
 &HT;    We call to your attention a new component of this wire: a
selection of several articles a day from a new business and
financial newsroom being operated jointly by The New York Times and
TheStreet.com.
 &HT;    The articles will be moving in the afternoon and are intended to
be the quickest coverage of the top financial news of the day.
 &HT;    Most days the stories will include a markets roundup, covering
the major developments in stocks, bonds, mutual funds, commodities
and the events that affect them. The goal is to make this story
available as soon as possible after the 4 p.m. ET close of the New
York exchanges.
 &HT;    Since its founding in 1996, TheStreet.com has become one of the
most closely watched of the the new Web-based providers of
financial news and commentary. It has 80 financial journalists
working in the headquarters on Wall Street, plus in bureaus in San
Francisco, Silicon Valley and London.
 &HT;    The New York Times and TheStreet.com opened their Wall Street
joint operation earlier this year, with reporters and editors
separate from those of both parent companies.
 &HT;    This staff has been generating breaking business coverage for
The Times' Web site, nytimes.com, and now those articles are being
added to this wire.
 &HT;    Just like the articles from our other partner news
organizations, the stories are available at no extra charge to all
clients of the New York Times News Service. They are moving with
this credit line:
 &HT;    c.2000 TheStreet.com/NYTimes.com
<TEXT>
