<SLUG> BC-BKN-NETS-KUPCHAK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NETS HAVE KUPCHAK ON LIST 
</HEADLINE>
   By CHRIS BROUSSARD   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New Jersey Nets have received permission from the Los
Angeles Lakers to speak with Lakers general manager Mitch Kupchak
about the Nets' director of basketball operations position, an
Eastern Conference executive said. Neither Lewis Katz, the Nets'
principal owner, nor Kupchak would comment, nor was it clear
whether the parties had already talked about the job.
</P>
<P>
   Kupchak, in his sixth season as the Lakers' general manager, is
one of several candidates the Nets view as a possible head of
basketball operations. Others the Nets are known to have an
interest in include Lenny Wilkens, John Thompson and Isiah Thomas,
though Thomas is thought to have more of an interest in coaching.
</P>
<P>
   Kupchak, 46, has been a member of the Lakers' front office since
retiring after a 10-year playing career in 1986. He signed a
long-term contract extension in 1998, but would perhaps consider
joining the Nets because of his East Coast background. He was born
in Hicksville, N.Y., and starred at Brentwood High School on Long
Island before embarking on an all-America career at the University
of North Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   The Nets are hoping to fill their director's position before the
NBA draft on June 28. The director's priorities will be to
determine whether to keep John Nash as the general manager and to
lead the search for a new head coach.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
